1
00:00:00,079 --> 00:00:02,841
Finally, the time I have
been waiting for is here.

2
00:00:02,866 --> 00:00:04,231
And what time is that?

3
00:00:04,797 --> 00:00:08,274
- Sometimes, people tend to space out.
- Right.

4
00:00:08,841 --> 00:00:11,301
And I keep thinking about this show.

5
00:00:11,326 --> 00:00:14,788
Last week's episode ended
with the appearance of Da-Na.

6
00:00:14,813 --> 00:00:16,625
- Right.
- Hello.

7
00:00:16,650 --> 00:00:19,207
I'm really curious about
what will happen next.

8
00:00:20,066 --> 00:00:21,066
Hello.

9
00:00:21,855 --> 00:00:26,618
When she showed up,
their eyes got all shiny.

10
00:00:26,845 --> 00:00:29,003
If I were there, I would've been upset.

11
00:00:29,028 --> 00:00:31,814
- Can you notice it?
- Isn't it so obvious?

12
00:00:31,839 --> 00:00:34,007
- It was so obvious.
- It was really clear.

13
00:00:34,032 --> 00:00:38,090
We found out that
Jung-woo is a Money Catcher.

14
00:00:39,793 --> 00:00:41,476
- That's right!
- It was a twist.

15
00:00:41,501 --> 00:00:43,272
And he even lied about his job.

16
00:00:43,465 --> 00:00:48,814
But the reason was because he wanted to
find true love. That was unexpected, too.

17
00:00:49,123 --> 00:00:52,523
Jung-woo may be a Money
Catcher, but he opened the

18
00:00:52,587 --> 00:00:57,531
possibility that he could
always turn into a Love Catcher.

19
00:00:57,608 --> 00:01:01,234
It makes me think he might
be a true Love Catcher.

20
00:01:01,931 --> 00:01:03,430
But where in Seoul is that?

21
00:01:04,026 --> 00:01:06,398
- Ui-dong.
- I see.

22
00:01:06,423 --> 00:01:08,695
That's where people usually
go for Membership Trainings.

23
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:10,228
It's near Ssangmun-dong.

24
00:01:11,105 --> 00:01:12,549
So it's in Ui-dong.

25
00:01:12,574 --> 00:01:15,315
(We're curious about the third
story of the Love Mansion today, too.)

26
00:01:15,940 --> 00:01:19,786
(A war-like romance unfolding
in the peaceful Seoul city)

27
00:01:19,986 --> 00:01:21,717
It's the morning of the second day.

28
00:01:21,742 --> 00:01:25,260
(This is the morning of the second day when
they'll take their first couple challenge.)

29
00:01:25,285 --> 00:01:27,048
(Men's lodging)

30
00:01:27,877 --> 00:01:30,743
(The guys haven't woken up
yet due to yesterday's aftermath.)

31
00:01:31,419 --> 00:01:32,419
(Jolt)

32
00:01:33,550 --> 00:01:37,305
- They spent their first day here, right?
- Right. It's their first morning.

33
00:01:37,330 --> 00:01:39,680
(Everyone is still sleeping.)

34
00:01:43,418 --> 00:01:46,846
- Jae-hyung is gone.
- Oh, he's not there.

35
00:01:48,074 --> 00:01:50,637
I don't know if I was just dreaming,

36
00:01:52,219 --> 00:01:54,258
but Jae-hyung seemed to be going out.

37
00:01:54,556 --> 00:01:56,127
Yeah, he wasn't here since 6 a.m.

38
00:01:56,152 --> 00:01:57,152
Yeah.

39
00:01:57,622 --> 00:02:01,939
(Where did he go early in the morning...?)

40
00:02:02,096 --> 00:02:04,699
I guess he has another plan up his sleeve.

41
00:02:05,178 --> 00:02:07,600
- I think he'll cook.
- Breakfast.

42
00:02:07,625 --> 00:02:08,973
- That's possible.
- Yes.

43
00:02:08,998 --> 00:02:10,721
(Women's lodging)

44
00:02:12,630 --> 00:02:13,828
It's Da-Na.

45
00:02:13,853 --> 00:02:17,417
(Da-Na and In-seong are
already up and getting ready.)

46
00:02:17,795 --> 00:02:20,922
- Do you usually wake up early?
- Yes.

47
00:02:21,306 --> 00:02:27,627
I usually sleep at 12 or 1
a.m. and wake up at 6 or 7 a.m.

48
00:02:27,652 --> 00:02:28,860
That's wonderful.

49
00:02:29,339 --> 00:02:31,339
But I kept tossing and turning last night.

50
00:02:34,013 --> 00:02:36,160
(Last night)

51
00:02:36,185 --> 00:02:38,490
(Da-Na arrived last when
everyone was about to go to bed.)

52
00:02:38,515 --> 00:02:40,990
- Hello!
- Hello!

53
00:02:41,494 --> 00:02:45,580
- It's nice to meet you.
- Hello.

54
00:02:46,133 --> 00:02:49,069
- She's gorgeous!
- She's like a model.

55
00:02:49,414 --> 00:02:51,421
- She's very ladylike.
- Hello.

56
00:02:52,048 --> 00:02:54,225
She's really attractive.

57
00:02:55,775 --> 00:02:57,451
She came to shake things up!

58
00:03:00,140 --> 00:03:02,933
Is there something you're
particularly worried about?

59
00:03:03,110 --> 00:03:04,110
Me?

60
00:03:05,612 --> 00:03:07,430
That I might not be able to adjust...

61
00:03:07,455 --> 00:03:08,455
I see!

62
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:11,632
I was worried that I'd
be the oldest one here.

63
00:03:12,786 --> 00:03:15,405
There's a lot of older women around me.

64
00:03:15,430 --> 00:03:18,441
- I see.
- I've never had a younger friend before.

65
00:03:19,897 --> 00:03:22,913
(Da-Na is worried about her
role as the oldest woman.)

66
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:28,759
But you really don't look
like the oldest among us.

67
00:03:29,711 --> 00:03:33,308
Seriously. You have amazing skin.

68
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:38,050
Are you the type to fall in love easily?

69
00:03:38,075 --> 00:03:39,687
- No.
- Me neither.

70
00:03:40,142 --> 00:03:42,547
I'm not the type to fall
for someone instantly.

71
00:03:42,835 --> 00:03:46,161
- Besides, life is unpredictable.
- I agree.

72
00:03:46,411 --> 00:03:50,269
It's only a week, but who knows what'll
happen if you keep sticking together?

73
00:03:50,294 --> 00:03:53,359
- Yeah, if you're constantly together...
- Right.

74
00:03:55,188 --> 00:03:56,988
It's still kind of awkward.

75
00:03:58,693 --> 00:04:03,228
(Are these two, who claim to not
fall in love easily, Money Catchers...?)

76
00:04:06,950 --> 00:04:09,550
(Shared dining room)

77
00:04:11,580 --> 00:04:13,192
They're cooking breakfast.

78
00:04:13,217 --> 00:04:17,361
- Where's Jae-hyung?
- Oh, did he really go out?

79
00:04:17,748 --> 00:04:22,015
Did he just leave the Love
Mansion, or did he leave the program?

80
00:04:23,387 --> 00:04:25,331
Does anyone eat breakfast here?

81
00:04:26,159 --> 00:04:29,158
I think a majority of them
just eat it if it's available.

82
00:04:31,555 --> 00:04:34,753
(After she answers, the silence returns.)

83
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:42,339
When you saw the guys for the first time,
was there someone who caught your eye?

84
00:04:43,141 --> 00:04:46,841
- Oh my god! - Did she
ask that with Jung-woo in mind?

85
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:50,060
Jung-woo, your seat's here.

86
00:04:51,248 --> 00:04:55,716
When she first saw him, she
looked at him really meaningfully.

87
00:04:55,741 --> 00:04:56,932
(Smile)

88
00:04:57,223 --> 00:04:59,714
To be honest, from the
way we see it, those two

89
00:04:59,739 --> 00:05:02,230
girls can't be entirely
happy to see each other.

90
00:05:02,848 --> 00:05:07,975
When you saw the guys for the first time,
was there someone who caught your eye?

91
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,168
(Who gave Da-Na a
good first impression...?)

92
00:05:10,568 --> 00:05:11,568
Me?

93
00:05:12,562 --> 00:05:13,562
Yes.

94
00:05:13,587 --> 00:05:15,321
Will she openly reveal it?

95
00:05:15,405 --> 00:05:19,502
I was just so out of it yesterday.

96
00:05:19,527 --> 00:05:21,119
I see, I see.

97
00:05:22,104 --> 00:05:24,971
- Honestly, I don't even remember
all their faces. - Really?

98
00:05:24,996 --> 00:05:26,989
I forgot all of their names, too.

99
00:05:27,022 --> 00:05:28,817
I think if we get a bit more comfortable,

100
00:05:29,270 --> 00:05:31,413
we'll get to know each other naturally.

101
00:05:31,835 --> 00:05:32,835
I see.

102
00:05:33,618 --> 00:05:37,030
Is she telling the truth, or
is she hiding her feelings?

103
00:05:37,055 --> 00:05:39,970
I'm sure she remembers Jung-woo's face.

104
00:05:40,910 --> 00:05:42,228
It's silent.

105
00:05:44,245 --> 00:05:47,190
(Just then, Su-won breaks
the silence and enters.)

106
00:05:47,752 --> 00:05:51,211
- What time did you wake up?
- I'm not sure.

107
00:05:52,264 --> 00:05:53,264
It's Su-won.

108
00:05:55,272 --> 00:05:56,366
(Glance)

109
00:05:59,201 --> 00:06:01,605
- Do you drink coffee in the morning?
- Yes, I love to.

110
00:06:01,630 --> 00:06:03,454
I wanted to drink it.

111
00:06:10,819 --> 00:06:14,282
(Su-won leisurely makes coffee.)

112
00:06:23,161 --> 00:06:25,121
- Is it done?
- I just put it in your cup.

113
00:06:25,146 --> 00:06:26,430
Thank you.

114
00:06:27,625 --> 00:06:29,792
(She takes a break with Su-won's coffee.)

115
00:06:29,817 --> 00:06:33,422
- Oh, do you want to help us?
- Sure, what can I do?

116
00:06:33,454 --> 00:06:37,285
You just have to add the ingredients.
The bread is sliced here.

117
00:06:37,310 --> 00:06:38,310
Okay.

118
00:06:39,733 --> 00:06:40,733
(Glance)

119
00:06:40,978 --> 00:06:42,383
(Reach)

120
00:06:42,850 --> 00:06:44,619
- So just put them in here?
- Yes.

121
00:06:44,644 --> 00:06:48,796
- But he only gave Da-Na coffee, right?
- Why not In-seong?

122
00:06:48,821 --> 00:06:49,821
Seriously.

123
00:06:50,779 --> 00:06:53,892
- Can I put them in here regardless
of order? - Yes, that's fine.

124
00:06:54,345 --> 00:06:56,734
They all end up in your mouth anyway.

125
00:06:57,087 --> 00:06:59,071
I don't think anyone will eat what I made.

126
00:06:59,828 --> 00:07:02,556
(Warm and cheerful)

127
00:07:03,532 --> 00:07:04,633
She's tall.

128
00:07:05,001 --> 00:07:06,863
She's not shy.

129
00:07:07,070 --> 00:07:09,263
She seems to have a bright personality.

130
00:07:09,982 --> 00:07:11,315
I think it was okay.

131
00:07:11,419 --> 00:07:13,459
What's going on? Is Su-won into her?

132
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:15,484
Is he trying to know about her?

133
00:07:18,362 --> 00:07:21,005
- Oh, it looks delicious!
- They made a yummy breakfast.

134
00:07:21,030 --> 00:07:22,858
(The first breakfast at the Love Mansion)

135
00:07:26,097 --> 00:07:27,353
This is awesome.

136
00:07:28,604 --> 00:07:31,107
- Did you make everything?
- When did she make all that?

137
00:07:31,132 --> 00:07:32,559
No, we cooked together.

138
00:07:32,584 --> 00:07:34,640
- With In-seong?
- Really?

139
00:07:34,665 --> 00:07:36,515
Wow, you did a great job!

140
00:07:36,540 --> 00:07:38,661
- I can't believe this.
- It looks incredible.

141
00:07:38,686 --> 00:07:40,186
Did they overwork themselves?

142
00:07:40,211 --> 00:07:43,379
Da-Na and In-seong, thank you.

143
00:07:43,698 --> 00:07:46,104
I'm not sure if I can eat this.

144
00:07:47,329 --> 00:07:51,730
Da-Na joined late, so she made
breakfast to get closer with everyone.

145
00:07:51,755 --> 00:07:53,437
She's making a lot of efforts.

146
00:07:54,670 --> 00:07:57,829
- Hello.
- Hello.

147
00:07:58,753 --> 00:08:00,923
- I'll have one.
- Go ahead.

148
00:08:00,948 --> 00:08:03,306
- Thank you.
- You can have two.

149
00:08:04,441 --> 00:08:05,893
(Nom)

150
00:08:08,864 --> 00:08:11,106
- It's really good.
- Pardon? It is?

151
00:08:11,658 --> 00:08:15,038
Da-Na scored a lot of
brownie points that morning.

152
00:08:16,139 --> 00:08:18,607
- Hello.
- Hello.

153
00:08:19,450 --> 00:08:21,603
- Did you make all this?
- Yes, she did.

154
00:08:21,628 --> 00:08:22,628
For real?

155
00:08:22,653 --> 00:08:25,258
All you have to do is wash the
veggies and put them in the bread.

156
00:08:25,283 --> 00:08:26,774
(Wide-eyed)

157
00:08:28,692 --> 00:08:30,343
Did you make the croissant, too?

158
00:08:30,662 --> 00:08:32,162
- Oh, that's...
- No way.

159
00:08:32,926 --> 00:08:34,720
I was going to lie.

160
00:08:36,581 --> 00:08:38,359
Da-Na has a great personality.

161
00:08:38,384 --> 00:08:43,281
Won-jae said that she looks
the closest to his ideal type.

162
00:08:43,897 --> 00:08:46,754
He's like, "On top of
that, she can even cook?"

163
00:08:46,779 --> 00:08:48,536
He can't help but like her.

164
00:08:48,561 --> 00:08:50,361
- How old are you?
- 23.

165
00:08:52,565 --> 00:08:55,056
Did you know he appeared on "Steel Troops"?

166
00:08:55,081 --> 00:08:56,449
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

167
00:08:58,698 --> 00:09:00,387
- Oh gosh!
- He's super shy!

168
00:09:00,412 --> 00:09:03,973
- Wow, are you an actor then?
- I'm sorry?

169
00:09:04,314 --> 00:09:07,419
- She doesn't know "Steel Troops."
- It's not a drama? I don't know.

170
00:09:07,444 --> 00:09:08,739
Is it a movie?

171
00:09:08,956 --> 00:09:10,487
Yes, it is.

172
00:09:11,490 --> 00:09:12,942
He's so cute.

173
00:09:15,374 --> 00:09:18,175
(Explaining the program)

174
00:09:18,767 --> 00:09:24,327
I'm not in the military right now.
I finished my mandatory service.

175
00:09:24,352 --> 00:09:25,352
I see.

176
00:09:25,829 --> 00:09:28,140
It's adorable that he
keeps trying to show her his charms.

177
00:09:29,144 --> 00:09:32,583
Jung-woo always comes at
the end like the man of the hour.

178
00:09:32,608 --> 00:09:37,522
Does he hide behind the wall
and listen for the cue to enter?

179
00:09:37,843 --> 00:09:41,272
- He was the last one to
come yesterday, too. - I know.

180
00:09:44,119 --> 00:09:45,119
(Peek)

181
00:09:47,137 --> 00:09:48,137
(Glance)

182
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:52,666
(He sits across from them
where they can see him.)

183
00:09:52,691 --> 00:09:54,081
Have a sandwich.

184
00:09:54,779 --> 00:09:55,916
(Hesitate)

185
00:09:59,691 --> 00:10:00,691
Thank you.

186
00:10:01,757 --> 00:10:03,131
She's taking care of him.

187
00:10:03,948 --> 00:10:05,768
In-seong might feel uncomfortable.

188
00:10:06,691 --> 00:10:09,104
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

189
00:10:13,585 --> 00:10:15,180
(Bite)

190
00:10:18,164 --> 00:10:22,164
- It tastes like the store-bought ones.
- Really? I appreciate it.

191
00:10:23,755 --> 00:10:24,755
(Glance)

192
00:10:24,780 --> 00:10:26,701
- She doesn't look happy.
- Oh no.

193
00:10:28,397 --> 00:10:32,529
(Da-Na reacts to his smallest movements.)

194
00:10:32,664 --> 00:10:35,354
She gave him a tissue really quickly.

195
00:10:36,013 --> 00:10:37,871
That means she's been watching him.

196
00:10:38,543 --> 00:10:39,543
You're quick.

197
00:10:40,083 --> 00:10:41,083
No, I'm not.

198
00:10:42,809 --> 00:10:44,816
Oh gosh. I'm upset for her.

199
00:10:45,268 --> 00:10:46,906
(Trying to smile)

200
00:10:47,807 --> 00:10:49,545
Isn't one of the guys missing?

201
00:10:49,570 --> 00:10:51,570
Is Jae-hyung still not coming?

202
00:10:52,009 --> 00:10:54,628
- I thought he was making breakfast.
- Did he go for a jog?

203
00:10:55,156 --> 00:10:56,156
Or a drive?

204
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:59,625
- Where did he go?
- Where is he?

205
00:11:01,255 --> 00:11:03,901
(At that time, Jae-hyung's
car is racing down the road.)

206
00:11:05,286 --> 00:11:08,690
I suddenly hate my Porsche.

207
00:11:10,282 --> 00:11:14,045
- I'm sorry.
- It's fine.

208
00:11:14,070 --> 00:11:16,232
After that humiliating
incident on the first day,

209
00:11:16,771 --> 00:11:19,038
I didn't want to drive it anymore.

210
00:11:19,579 --> 00:11:21,379
Oh, because of that memory?

211
00:11:22,137 --> 00:11:23,589
Then what is he gonna do?

212
00:11:27,785 --> 00:11:29,650
Lamborghinis are the best.

213
00:11:30,764 --> 00:11:31,835
Holy crap.

214
00:11:33,051 --> 00:11:34,118
He planned that.

215
00:11:34,143 --> 00:11:36,475
(His plan has entirely changed.)

216
00:11:38,131 --> 00:11:42,401
I brought a different car for
the date with a different woman.

217
00:11:42,897 --> 00:11:44,523
He had a reason for doing that.

218
00:11:44,548 --> 00:11:47,166
(Who do you hope to go on a date with?)

219
00:11:47,191 --> 00:11:48,191
Da-Na?

220
00:11:49,452 --> 00:11:55,031
She's my next target.
So this is just the beginning.

221
00:11:56,086 --> 00:11:57,680
What do you think about that?

222
00:11:57,705 --> 00:12:00,446
- It's like magic.
- Poof.

223
00:12:00,471 --> 00:12:03,550
His car turned into a
Lamborghini after a few hours.

224
00:12:03,575 --> 00:12:05,020
This is just the beginning.

225
00:12:06,555 --> 00:12:08,325
- Hello.
- Hello.

226
00:12:09,092 --> 00:12:10,893
Hello!

227
00:12:11,340 --> 00:12:14,577
- Hi, where'd you go?
- I went home for a bit.

228
00:12:14,805 --> 00:12:15,995
- Oh.
- Oh.

229
00:12:17,218 --> 00:12:20,139
- Why did you go home?
- To change my car.

230
00:12:20,164 --> 00:12:22,442
Sorry?
Did he say he changed his car?

231
00:12:22,597 --> 00:12:24,074
He went to change his car.

232
00:12:27,441 --> 00:12:28,592
(Fascinated)

233
00:12:30,149 --> 00:12:32,312
(Da-na's sandwich is
right in front of Jae-hyung.)

234
00:12:32,769 --> 00:12:34,831
(Stare)

235
00:12:35,148 --> 00:12:38,351
- Did you make this yourself?
- Yes. We made it together.

236
00:12:38,620 --> 00:12:40,479
- Really?
- They left one for him.

237
00:12:40,582 --> 00:12:42,187
It must have been a lot of work.

238
00:12:42,212 --> 00:12:43,499
- That's it?
- Huh?

239
00:12:43,755 --> 00:12:45,707
- Is that all you're gonna say?
- Thank you.

240
00:12:47,712 --> 00:12:50,926
- Jae-hyung looks happy.
- Right, he got brighter.

241
00:12:51,692 --> 00:12:53,406
That security footage was really scary.

242
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:56,734
So from the beginning, it
was four girls and five guys?

243
00:12:58,691 --> 00:13:02,961
- That's why I was lonely.
- Oh, really? Why?

244
00:13:05,388 --> 00:13:07,602
The first day was really cruel. Seriously.

245
00:13:07,627 --> 00:13:09,414
What we did in the morning was cruel.

246
00:13:09,439 --> 00:13:12,568
- No, it was the dinner date.
- Gosh, I'm sorry.

247
00:13:14,348 --> 00:13:17,239
(Last night's painful
memory left a scar in him.)

248
00:13:17,264 --> 00:13:19,440
- Goodness. Su-won.
- Aww.

249
00:13:19,465 --> 00:13:21,141
I can't look in your direction.

250
00:13:21,166 --> 00:13:23,269
(Troubled)

251
00:13:24,380 --> 00:13:27,677
- Sorry for saying it from my POV.
- He must have been really upset.

252
00:13:27,702 --> 00:13:29,388
I'm really sorry.

253
00:13:29,745 --> 00:13:31,739
It could go the other way.

254
00:13:32,170 --> 00:13:33,558
That'd make it more interesting.

255
00:13:34,617 --> 00:13:36,323
- Oh my.
- Sorry.

256
00:13:36,786 --> 00:13:39,747
(Meanwhile, Ji-min is
washing the dishes by himself.)

257
00:13:44,866 --> 00:13:46,199
I'll do it now.

258
00:13:46,374 --> 00:13:47,875
It's a bit awkward to switch now.

259
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:51,410
- Why? I'll do this.
- Alright.

260
00:13:51,435 --> 00:13:53,349
- Ji-min, Ji-min?
- I like that.

261
00:13:54,687 --> 00:13:57,242
Do we have to wipe the water
droplets before putting them away?

262
00:13:57,562 --> 00:13:59,324
- That'd be nice.
- Right?

263
00:13:59,349 --> 00:14:01,239
- Do we have that?
- We have paper towel.

264
00:14:02,377 --> 00:14:04,036
Sorry, but can you push up my sleeves?

265
00:14:05,808 --> 00:14:07,260
(Sweet)

266
00:14:07,285 --> 00:14:09,605
- She's sweet.
- Things like that makes my heart flutter.

267
00:14:09,630 --> 00:14:10,811
The other side, too?

268
00:14:10,836 --> 00:14:14,195
She's been mustering the
courage ever since last night.

269
00:14:15,770 --> 00:14:18,853
Did you date a lot when
you were in college?

270
00:14:18,878 --> 00:14:20,609
No, I went to engineering school.

271
00:14:20,634 --> 00:14:22,367
You are? Oh, that's right.

272
00:14:24,595 --> 00:14:27,306
- So group dates and department
dates? - I did them a lot.

273
00:14:27,331 --> 00:14:29,069
Not department dates.
I did a lot of group

274
00:14:29,094 --> 00:14:30,872
dates when I was
younger. Oh, when I was 21.

275
00:14:31,249 --> 00:14:32,249
(Nod)

276
00:14:33,299 --> 00:14:35,577
Don't you do a lot of group dates, too?

277
00:14:36,180 --> 00:14:37,537
I don't know yet.

278
00:14:38,813 --> 00:14:40,662
I envy you. You're a college student.

279
00:14:41,252 --> 00:14:42,657
I loved college.

280
00:14:44,001 --> 00:14:47,485
They're nine years apart.

281
00:14:48,398 --> 00:14:51,858
I gave my Love Coin to Ji-min.

282
00:14:53,690 --> 00:14:55,042
(21 years old...)

283
00:14:55,928 --> 00:14:58,990
(Since she's young, she doesn't
calculate. She's faithful to her feelings.)

284
00:15:00,034 --> 00:15:01,034
I want to sit here, too.

285
00:15:04,825 --> 00:15:07,380
- Just enough to cover them.
- Okay, just this much.

286
00:15:07,939 --> 00:15:10,264
I'll give you some more
meat. I'll do it for you.

287
00:15:12,618 --> 00:15:15,762
I think he's more interested in them.

288
00:15:16,039 --> 00:15:17,391
That's how I felt.

289
00:15:17,775 --> 00:15:19,918
- It's a bit awkward to switch now.
- Why?

290
00:15:19,943 --> 00:15:22,943
(That's why she wanted
to get closer to him.)

291
00:15:24,163 --> 00:15:27,329
So to him, I'm just like a
little sister. That's about it.

292
00:15:29,351 --> 00:15:34,328
Right now, I'm the
ambassador of my university.

293
00:15:34,353 --> 00:15:35,353
You are?

294
00:15:36,064 --> 00:15:37,064
Same here.

295
00:15:37,460 --> 00:15:39,359
I'm the ambassador of
Sungkyunkwan University.

296
00:15:40,310 --> 00:15:43,616
(That's why she tried
to find a similarity.)

297
00:15:44,224 --> 00:15:47,192
I still have a chance with him,

298
00:15:47,867 --> 00:15:51,800
so it'll be nice to talk more with
him during the time we have left.

299
00:15:52,567 --> 00:15:57,003
I feel like his heart will change if she
keeps expressing her feelings to him.

300
00:15:58,198 --> 00:15:59,388
Do your best.

301
00:16:01,743 --> 00:16:05,227
This is for sure. Ever since Da-Na
came, everything's been changing.

302
00:16:05,252 --> 00:16:06,554
The mood is totally different.

303
00:16:06,579 --> 00:16:10,415
First off, Jae-hyung
changed his target right away.

304
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:13,537
But ever since they entered
the Love Mansion, we

305
00:16:13,562 --> 00:16:16,657
didn't get to really see
Su-won and Ha-neul talk.

306
00:16:17,013 --> 00:16:21,592
After they moved in there, it's
been a bit quiet between them.

307
00:16:21,725 --> 00:16:25,910
Like the coffee. He just made one
for Da-Na. That's weighing on my mind.

308
00:16:25,935 --> 00:16:26,935
Right.

309
00:16:27,174 --> 00:16:29,896
I have no idea about Ahn
Ji-min's feelings either.

310
00:16:30,257 --> 00:16:34,384
I'm not sure if he likes Ha-neul or Ji-min.

311
00:16:35,071 --> 00:16:37,491
He's the most veiled one.

312
00:16:37,730 --> 00:16:42,846
At first, Ahn Ji-min
thought Ha-neul was young.

313
00:16:43,461 --> 00:16:46,287
I'm 27 years old.

314
00:16:46,718 --> 00:16:48,918
But after she revealed her age...

315
00:16:49,540 --> 00:16:50,992
I'll give you more meat.

316
00:16:51,017 --> 00:16:53,262
He started taking care of her more.

317
00:16:53,287 --> 00:16:58,884
So I believe he's interested in her.

318
00:17:00,721 --> 00:17:03,145
(Peaceful morning free time)

319
00:17:04,221 --> 00:17:06,515
- That scared me.
- There's something on the screen.

320
00:17:07,225 --> 00:17:12,764
Before you came, that screen
came on like 20 times! Seriously.

321
00:17:12,975 --> 00:17:14,666
We're doing a challenge today.

322
00:17:15,233 --> 00:17:18,813
- I'm so curious.
- It's probably her first time seeing it.

323
00:17:18,838 --> 00:17:21,299
(Today's Couple Challenge:
Couple Photo Shoot)

324
00:17:21,324 --> 00:17:25,270
- I knew it.
- That's our signature challenge.

325
00:17:27,901 --> 00:17:30,064
I wonder how the couples
will be chosen this time.

326
00:17:30,234 --> 00:17:31,312
(Relaxed)

327
00:17:31,584 --> 00:17:32,885
- What?
- What?

328
00:17:33,203 --> 00:17:34,203
What's wrong?

329
00:17:35,211 --> 00:17:36,245
What's that?

330
00:17:36,270 --> 00:17:39,311
